I am building a web application and I am trying to create a function that checks whether a user is authenticated before allowing them to access certain routes. I am using Node.js and Express.js. Here is my code so far:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

// Set up authentication middleware
const authenticate = (req, res, next) => {
  // Check if user is authenticated
  if (req.isAuthenticated()) {
    return next();
  } else {
    res.redirect('/login');
  }
};

// Routes
app.get('/', authenticate, (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello, authenticated user!');
});

app.get('/login', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Please log in');
});

// Start the server
app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server listening on port ${port}`);
});
```

However, I am getting an error saying that `req.isAuthenticated()` is not a function. What is the issue and how can I fix it?

